Serializable
public class AmmpServiceException
extends AmmpClientException

Represents an Exception that occurred because of an error with a service that the AmmpClient was attempting to communicate with. Generally speaking this class should not be thrown directly but rather the developer should use the proper Builder or Factory on AmmpClientException in order to generate this method via the services response status code.
